    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yes, setting up granular distributed tracing is the perfect way to catch these \"invisible\" moments, and you should definitely start by instrumenting your `payment-gateway-auth` calls with tools like OpenTelemetry or Jaeger. This will let you see exactly where the request stalls—whether it's stuck in your connection pool, waiting on a TLS handshake, or hanging in the gateway's internal queue.\n\nTo make this even more effective, you should enable **span context propagation** across your microservices so that a single trace ID follows the request from your frontend, through your API, all the way to the payment gateway. This way, if a request \"disappears,\" the trace will show you the exact point where the span stops or times out, revealing whether the issue is upstream or downstream.\n\n*Note: You might also want to enable **trace sampling** specifically for high-traffic periods or when errors are detected, so you don't lose visibility on the very moments when the system is under stress.*\n\n**Why this matters:**\n*   **Pinpointing the Black Hole:** Without tracing, you're guessing; with it, you can see the exact millisecond the connection hangs.\n*   **Resource Contention",
